    <h2>Structures</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>An extension to the standard Elks <i>ARRAY </i>class that
        allows memory area sharing on sub arrays. Possible to see up to
        a 100% performance increase on digital processing applications
        which make heavy use of ARRAYs. (Standard Elks subarray function
        makes a copy of the subarray. Safe but not very efficient.) </li>
      <li>Memory efficient form of numeric lists with many repeats
        implemented as run length encoded arrayed lists.</li>
      <li>Numeric array serialization.</li>
    </ul>
